  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the income of the poorest and the health status of vulnerable communities in Manono Territory, Katanga, DRC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cash for work for roads and bridges rehabilitation, WASH, FIM</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The contextual analysis identified four groups of extreme poor, who will be targeted by this programme: (i) households reliant on small contracts and casual labour for subsistence, (ii) Female-headed households, in particular widows and young women abandoned by their husbands, (iii) The Bashimbi minority ethnic group, (iv) People who lack the physical capacity to support themselves through agriculture: the elderly, disabled and chronically ill. Efforts will be made to improve farming practices to improve fertility and yield to complement alternative income generation sources, as well as boosting local markets and creating linkages with regional traders. Both Context Analyses identified household labour deficiency and access to land as key determinants of extreme poverty. Consequently, programming in both contexts will aim to improve income and develop resilient asset bases through non-labour intensive approaches such as communal agriculture and off-farm income generation opportunities.The overall goal of the programme is to enhance households&apos; income and access to markets, improve access to water, hygiene and sanitation practices and improve the status of vulnerable and marginalized groups.</narrative>
  </description>
